{"overview":"This compact binary piece in A major unfolds with a graceful, song-like character anchored by an Alberti-style accompaniment beneath a lyrical melodic line; its most distinctive feature is the mid-piece tonicization of the dominant E major in bars 13–16, where the returning A-theme is reharmonized to create a sense of brightened expansion before the coda reaffirms the home key.","cross_piece_tags":["binary","lyrical","meditative","intimate","alberti_bass","circle_of_fifths","theme_and_variations"]}
